h3 Content Tabs

p
  | Content tabs are used to separate content into visually exclusive sections that can be accessed via a single content area.
  <br>They provide a flat navigation structure for content, without requiring a page refresh on change.

p
  | Content tabs should be used in cases where only one tab's content would be of individual interest to the user.
  <br>In cases where the user is expected to sequentially move through all tabs (rather than just selecting one), a wizard is more appropriate.

.component
  ul.nav.nav-tabs
    li.active
      a href='#content-tabs-kame' data-toggle='tab' Kame
    li
      a href='#content-tabs-hame' data-toggle='tab' Hame
    li
      a href='#content-tabs-haaa' data-toggle='tab' Haaa
  .tab-content
    #content-tabs-kame.tab-pane.active
      .panel-body
        h2 Kame...
    #content-tabs-hame.tab-pane
      .panel-body
        h2 ...hame...
    #content-tabs-haaa.tab-pane
      .panel-body
        h2 ...HAAAaaa!

